data.title: George Papandreou resigns as Greek prime minister - video
data.meta_description: Greek prime minister tells the Greek people in a television address to the nation shortly before his resignation that it is vital politicians co-operate
data.text:
This article is more than 12 years old

The prime minister tells the Greek people in a television address to the nation shortly before his resignation that it is vital that politicians co-operate. Papandreou insisted that he sought to work with other politicians from the start of the crisis and that he's done a good job as prime minister. He said that Greece had avoided the "sure bankruptcy" that would surely have resulted without the bailout deals agreed
